  "text": "We also examined the effects of the second messenger of PGE [CITATION_1] animals are shown in Fig. 5 A more definitive PGE 2 effect on Ca 2ϩ influx is indicated by data in Fig. 6 . Thapsigargin, which presumably inhibited Ca 2ϩ uptake into the intracellular reservoir and caused depletion of the reservoir, allowed for the monitoring of Ca 2ϩ influx after CaCl 2 was added to the extracellular compartment. Figure 6 shows a cessation of the Ca 2ϩ influx with the reintroduction of additional quantities of EGTA. PGE 2 addition after CaCl 2 was evidently effective in attenuating the influx of Ca 2ϩ .",
